Step 1. Calculate Gross Profit Margin:
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 8,372,608.70 and Total Revenue = 28,572,608.70.
• So, 8,372,608.70 / 28,572,608.70 ≈ 0.2932, which is 29.32% when multiplied by 100.

Step 2. Calculate Operating Cash Flow Ratio:
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Current Liabilities)
• From the cash flow, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -10,442,735.47.
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 8,028,630.43.
• Thus, -10,442,735.47 / 8,028,630.43 ≈ -1.30.

Presenting the final answer in the required JSON format:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "29.32%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-1.30"
  }
}
